    <item>
      <title>Ball on Small Plate</title>
      <link>https://chengzhag.github.io/project/ball_on_small_plate/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 04 Jun 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://chengzhag.github.io/project/ball_on_small_plate/</guid>
      <description>&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ball on Small Plate is built with a Raspberry Zero, a camera, two servos, a STM32F103 board, and is capable of setting target coordinate, circling around the center with adjustable radius.
This project is a work of team of 3, which includes &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/shicaiwei123&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;shicaiwei123&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/yoyolalala&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;yoyolalala&lt;/a&gt;.
Code and documents are available &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/pidan1231239/ball_on_plate&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. Platform details are discussed &lt;a href=&#34;https://chengzhag.github.io/project/ball_on_big_plate/&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;demo&#34;&gt;Demo&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;iframe src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/UgZbSz2ecN0&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; allowfullscreen title=&#34;YouTube Video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;mechanical-structure&#34;&gt;Mechanical structure&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;first-version&#34;&gt;First version&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The 20cm*20cm plate is made of 1mm black glass fiber board. In the first version shown in the video, the plate is covered with white paper to provide more contrast between ball and plate. Below shows the original plate.&lt;/p&gt;














&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-deisigning-the-mechanical-structure&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;
        &lt;img alt=&#34;Deisigning the mechanical structure&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/IMG_20170619_162559_huee1120c721bb8f208075eae0c50a4226_1718480_9a44171a6b959f75373c7459b606941f.jpg 400w,
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/IMG_20170619_162559_huee1120c721bb8f208075eae0c50a4226_1718480_f36fd04c346bfa9d1a5f3c0e5a1fa9a8.jpg 760w,
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/IMG_20170619_162559_huee1120c721bb8f208075eae0c50a4226_1718480_1200x1200_fit_q75_lanczos.jpg 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://chengzhag.github.io/project/ball_on_small_plate/IMG_20170619_162559_huee1120c721bb8f208075eae0c50a4226_1718480_9a44171a6b959f75373c7459b606941f.jpg&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;570&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      Deisigning the mechanical structure
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The plate is supported with a universal joint in the center and has 2 degrees of freedom. The angle of the plate is controled by two servos with ball joint rods connecting the servos and the plate.&lt;/p&gt;














&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-installation-of-plate-and-two-servos&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;
        &lt;img alt=&#34;Installation of plate and two servos&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/IMG_20170619_172950_huf3367135c0755eb0dcffd44cde0ceb3b_3899672_32805882de131fe90af0377c4a98e24e.jpg 400w,
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/IMG_20170619_172950_huf3367135c0755eb0dcffd44cde0ceb3b_3899672_7e2c37ace75def3d7b55b2558d5d88c8.jpg 760w,
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/IMG_20170619_172950_huf3367135c0755eb0dcffd44cde0ceb3b_3899672_1200x1200_fit_q75_lanczos.jpg 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://chengzhag.github.io/project/ball_on_small_plate/IMG_20170619_172950_huf3367135c0755eb0dcffd44cde0ceb3b_3899672_32805882de131fe90af0377c4a98e24e.jpg&#34;
               width=&#34;570&#34;
               height=&#34;760&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      Installation of plate and two servos
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this first version. The camera is fixed to the base, which requires extra procedure to segment the plate from background and warp back to squre. This introduces noise to the positioning of the ball, which is the major reason for the jittering in the video.&lt;/p&gt;














&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-installation-of-camera-and-raspberry-pi-zero&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;
        &lt;img alt=&#34;Installation of camera and Raspberry Pi Zero&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/cap_VID_20170624_154918_00_00_02_01_hud7bbec429c3ed9e6a9e4bd567b79a25d_147483_fd3a12a7a76310e5836123ab0b44b8b8.jpg 400w,
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/cap_VID_20170624_154918_00_00_02_01_hud7bbec429c3ed9e6a9e4bd567b79a25d_147483_fb5c4efcf7fa5f511329c638ef257b21.jpg 760w,
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/cap_VID_20170624_154918_00_00_02_01_hud7bbec429c3ed9e6a9e4bd567b79a25d_147483_1200x1200_fit_q75_lanczos.jpg 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://chengzhag.github.io/project/ball_on_small_plate/cap_VID_20170624_154918_00_00_02_01_hud7bbec429c3ed9e6a9e4bd567b79a25d_147483_fd3a12a7a76310e5836123ab0b44b8b8.jpg&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;428&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      Installation of camera and Raspberry Pi Zero
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;second-version&#34;&gt;Second version&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By fixing the camera to the plate with carbon fiber tubes, we managed to avoid the noise. The Raspberry Pi 3b is hanged beyond the camera to reduce the load on the servos. The plate itself is also changed to yellow thus no paper is needed. This reduces friction between the ball and the plate.&lt;/p&gt;














&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-camera-is-connected-to-the-plate-to-reduce-jitter&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;
        &lt;img alt=&#34;Camera is connected to the plate to reduce jitter&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/8_hu893020c1b70a6d9d85814ad6d70ccaf3_150552_a73bbb2deddb2277352a996e7083ece9.jpg 400w,
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/8_hu893020c1b70a6d9d85814ad6d70ccaf3_150552_33725ba751af1dec8762feec47ca5780.jpg 760w,
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/8_hu893020c1b70a6d9d85814ad6d70ccaf3_150552_1200x1200_fit_q75_lanczos.jpg 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://chengzhag.github.io/project/ball_on_small_plate/8_hu893020c1b70a6d9d85814ad6d70ccaf3_150552_a73bbb2deddb2277352a996e7083ece9.jpg&#34;
               width=&#34;571&#34;
               height=&#34;760&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      Camera is connected to the plate to reduce jitter
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A ring light is installed around the camera for better illumination.&lt;/p&gt;














&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-camera-and-led-installation&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;
        &lt;img alt=&#34;Camera and LED installation&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/6_huc54370fea8ce56218cbdfffe57a7de1c_26160_de738f3c511c9095b5f52bc5eca76199.jpg 400w,
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/6_huc54370fea8ce56218cbdfffe57a7de1c_26160_1d9aa333467529f53134d863228e3d71.jpg 760w,
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/6_huc54370fea8ce56218cbdfffe57a7de1c_26160_1200x1200_fit_q75_lanczos.jpg 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://chengzhag.github.io/project/ball_on_small_plate/6_huc54370fea8ce56218cbdfffe57a7de1c_26160_de738f3c511c9095b5f52bc5eca76199.jpg&#34;
               width=&#34;574&#34;
               height=&#34;429&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      Camera and LED installation
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Below shows the PCB board installed on the base, which is later used in project &lt;a href=&#34;https://chengzhag.github.io/project/ball_on_big_plate/&#34;&gt;Ball on Big Plate&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;














&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-pcb-mother-board&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;
        &lt;img alt=&#34;PCB mother board&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/ball_on_big_plate_pcb_huc3da0135bebb0686444372f5df76b114_56909_a351bed299fa01d08441058b05c329eb.jpg 400w,
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/ball_on_big_plate_pcb_huc3da0135bebb0686444372f5df76b114_56909_ace9bdf6babb28234664ecae0ff64f8a.jpg 760w,
               /project/ball_on_small_plate/ball_on_big_plate_pcb_huc3da0135bebb0686444372f5df76b114_56909_1200x1200_fit_q75_lanczos.jpg 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://chengzhag.github.io/project/ball_on_small_plate/ball_on_big_plate_pcb_huc3da0135bebb0686444372f5df76b114_56909_a351bed299fa01d08441058b05c329eb.jpg&#34;
               width=&#34;422&#34;
               height=&#34;540&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      PCB mother board
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
