    <item>
      <title>Rotary Inverted Pendulum</title>
      <link>https://chengzhag.github.io/project/rotary_inverted_pendulum/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 09 Apr 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://chengzhag.github.io/project/rotary_inverted_pendulum/</guid>
      <description>&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rotary Inverted Pendulum is built with an encoder, a brush motor, a STM32F103 board, and has no rotation limit. It is capable of setting target angle, non-stop swinging and automatically swinging up.
This project is a work of team of 3, which includes &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/shicaiwei123&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;shicaiwei123&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/yoyolalala&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;yoyolalala&lt;/a&gt;.
Code and documents are available &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/pidan1231239/inverted_pendulum&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. Platform details Code and documents are available &lt;a href=&#34;https://chengzhag.github.io/project/ball_on_big_plate/&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;demo&#34;&gt;Demo&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;iframe src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/R4VLmF_X5qM&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; allowfullscreen title=&#34;YouTube Video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;mechanical-structure&#34;&gt;Mechanical structure&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An optical encoder is used to measure the angle of the pendulum. Thus calibration needs to be down by relaxing the pendulum to get the absolute angle every time after reset.&lt;/p&gt;














&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-optical-encoder&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;
        &lt;img alt=&#34;Optical encoder&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/rotary_inverted_pendulum/IMG_20170409_204205_hu29a20b0968d69d10407c7466beaac138_239947_bccfc1d3fb70d4b69a668e86d80cef72.jpg 400w,
               /project/rotary_inverted_pendulum/IMG_20170409_204205_hu29a20b0968d69d10407c7466beaac138_239947_2e90878c6482a3e2229eafbc304c4182.jpg 760w,
               /project/rotary_inverted_pendulum/IMG_20170409_204205_hu29a20b0968d69d10407c7466beaac138_239947_1200x1200_fit_q75_lanczos.jpg 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://chengzhag.github.io/project/rotary_inverted_pendulum/IMG_20170409_204205_hu29a20b0968d69d10407c7466beaac138_239947_bccfc1d3fb70d4b69a668e86d80cef72.jpg&#34;
               width=&#34;20%&#34;
               height=&#34;760&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      Optical encoder
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A slip ring (or collector ring) is used to prevent the winding of the wire.&lt;/p&gt;














&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-slip-ring&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;
        &lt;img alt=&#34;Slip ring&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/rotary_inverted_pendulum/%E7%A8%BF%E5%AE%9A%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%E5%AF%BC%E5%87%BA-20180604-225745_hu51376fd6dc65ca3962c7bb8478d63935_22574_bdec35728bec195e5da368e4421b480f.jpg 400w,
               /project/rotary_inverted_pendulum/%E7%A8%BF%E5%AE%9A%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%E5%AF%BC%E5%87%BA-20180604-225745_hu51376fd6dc65ca3962c7bb8478d63935_22574_d2c969277c6bb9288f06d45f819c6074.jpg 760w,
               /project/rotary_inverted_pendulum/%E7%A8%BF%E5%AE%9A%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%E5%AF%BC%E5%87%BA-20180604-225745_hu51376fd6dc65ca3962c7bb8478d63935_22574_1200x1200_fit_q75_lanczos.jpg 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://chengzhag.github.io/project/rotary_inverted_pendulum/%E7%A8%BF%E5%AE%9A%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%E5%AF%BC%E5%87%BA-20180604-225745_hu51376fd6dc65ca3962c7bb8478d63935_22574_bdec35728bec195e5da368e4421b480f.jpg&#34;
               width=&#34;20%&#34;
               height=&#34;311&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      Slip ring
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The DC brush motor with reduction gearbox and magnetic encoder is driven by a TB6612FNG model controlled controled with PWM signal. A 3-ceils lithium battery is used as power.&lt;/p&gt;














&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-complete-circuit-board&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;
        &lt;img alt=&#34;Complete circuit board&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/rotary_inverted_pendulum/IMG_20170504_112659_hu79c3b519b802e18d27a72aba7aa84a64_3289927_4c655b0a37c440c9abde2b7838a41c03.jpg 400w,
